<div class="article-modal-overlay" id="articleModalOverlay" onclick="if(event.target===this) closeArticle();">
  <div class="article-modal">
    <button class="article-modal-close" onclick="closeArticle()" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
    <div id="articleModalContent"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  const articles = {
    idempotency: {
      title: "Why Every Backend Developer Should Understand Idempotency Before Building Payment Systems",
      meta: "June 2026 &middot; 8 min read",
      body: "<blockquote>One of the biggest lessons I learned while integrating M-Pesa wasn't about APIs - it was about a distributed systems concept called idempotency. Once I understood it, it changed how I designed every backend system.</blockquote><h3>The Theory</h3><p>In distributed systems, a request can be delivered more than once.</p><p>Not because the client wants it to.</p><p>Because networks fail.</p><p>Imagine you're buying coffee using your mobile banking app. You tap Pay. The money leaves your account. At the exact same moment, your internet connection drops. Your phone never receives confirmation.</p><p>What do you do? You press Pay again.</p><p>Did you intend to pay twice? No. But from the server's perspective, it has now received two separate payment requests.</p>"
    },
    'school-disputes': {
      title: "How a School Management System Reduces Payment Disputes by 70%",
      meta: "July 2026 &middot; 6 min read",
      body: "<p>Payment disputes are one of the biggest administrative challenges in schools. Parents insist they have paid, accountants struggle to verify transactions, and students sometimes face unnecessary delays because payments cannot be confirmed quickly.</p><p>The good news is that these disputes are largely preventable with a modern School Management System integrated with M-Pesa.</p><h3>Why Payment Disputes Happen</h3><p>Most payment disputes are not caused by missing money. They happen because of manual processes such as:</p><ul><li>Recording payments by hand.</li><li>Updating fee balances later instead of instantly.</li><li>Entering the wrong admission number.</li><li>Duplicate payment entries.</li><li>Delayed confirmation of successful transactions.</li></ul><p>As the number of students grows, these small mistakes become more frequent and consume valuable administrative time.</p><h3>How Modern Systems Solve the Problem</h3><p>A School Management System automates the entire payment process from the moment a parent completes an M-Pesa payment.</p><p>Once the transaction is successful, Safaricom sends a secure notification, known as a webhook, directly to the school's system. The system then automatically:</p><ul><li>Records the payment.</li><li>Updates the student's fee balance.</li><li>Generates a digital receipt.</li><li>Updates the parent and student portals.</li><li>Stores the transaction in an audit log.</li></ul><p>This happens within seconds without requiring manual intervention.</p><h3>Preventing Duplicate Payments</h3><p>Reliable systems also protect schools from duplicate transactions.</p><p>Every M-Pesa payment includes a unique transaction reference. Before recording a payment, the system checks whether that reference already exists.</p><p>If it does, the payment is ignored. If it doesn't, it is recorded once. This process, called idempotency, ensures that one payment always produces one receipt, even if the payment confirmation is received multiple times.</p><h3>What Happens If the Internet Fails?</h3><p>Temporary internet outages should never result in lost payments.</p><p>A well-designed system automatically retries failed operations until the payment is successfully processed. Parents do not need to pay again, and accountants do not need to enter transactions manually.</p><h3>The Result</h3><p>By replacing manual fee processing with automated payment verification, schools can significantly reduce payment disputes while improving efficiency.</p><p>Benefits include:</p><ul><li>Faster payment confirmation.</li><li>Accurate fee balances.</li><li>Fewer manual errors.</li><li>Instant digital receipts.</li><li>Complete transaction history.</li><li>Better financial reporting.</li><li>Increased trust from parents and staff.</li></ul>"
    },
    'multi-tenant': {
      title: "Multi-Tenant Architecture: One Codebase, Many Schools",
      meta: "July 2026 &middot; 5 min read",
      body: "<p>As more schools adopt cloud-based software, building a separate system for every institution quickly becomes expensive and difficult to maintain. That's why modern School Management Systems use multi-tenant architecture - a design where one application securely serves many schools at the same time.</p><h3>What Is Multi-Tenant Architecture?</h3><p>A multi-tenant system allows multiple schools to use the same software while keeping each school's data completely separate.</p><p>For example, School A cannot access students, payments, or reports belonging to School B. Although they share the same application, each institution only sees its own information.</p><h3>How It Works</h3><p>When a school logs in, the system identifies which institution the user belongs to. Every request, from viewing students to processing M-Pesa payments, is automatically filtered to that school.</p><p>This means:</p><ul><li>Student records stay private.</li><li>Fee payments belong to the correct school.</li><li>Reports are generated per institution.</li><li>Staff only access their own school's data.</li></ul><p>Data never crosses from one school to another.</p><h3>Why It Matters</h3><p>A multi-tenant platform offers major advantages for both software providers and schools:</p><ul><li>Lower hosting costs.</li><li>Faster software updates for every school.</li><li>Easier maintenance with one codebase.</li><li>Consistent security across all institutions.</li><li>Simple onboarding of new schools without deploying a new application.</li></ul><p>Instead of managing dozens of separate systems, developers maintain one platform that scales as more schools join.</p><h3>Security Comes First</h3><p>The success of a multi-tenant system depends on strong data isolation. Every database query, API request, and user session must be linked to the correct school to prevent unauthorized access.</p><p>When implemented correctly, each school experiences the platform as if it were built exclusively for them.</p><h3>Final Thoughts</h3><p>Multi-tenant architecture is the foundation of modern education SaaS platforms. It allows thousands of schools to use the same application while keeping their data secure, isolated, and easy to manage.</p><p>For schools, it means reliable, affordable software. For providers, it means a scalable platform that grows without increasing operational complexity.</p>"
    },
    'spreadsheets-software': {
      title: "Spreadsheets to Software: When It's Time to Upgrade",
      meta: "July 2026 &middot; 4 min read",
      body: "<p>Spreadsheets have helped businesses manage finances, customers, inventory, and daily operations for decades. They're affordable, flexible, and easy to start with. But as a business grows, spreadsheets often become a bottleneck instead of a solution.</p><p>The challenge isn't that spreadsheets are bad - it's that they weren't designed to run an entire business.</p><p>So, how do you know it's time to upgrade?</p><h3>1. You're Entering the Same Data More Than Once</h3><p>If your team copies information between multiple spreadsheets, emails, or paper records, you're losing time every day.</p><p>The more manual data entry involved, the greater the chance of mistakes. A missed digit, duplicate entry, or accidental deletion can lead to incorrect reports and costly decisions.</p><p>A business system stores information once and updates it everywhere it's needed.</p><h3>2. Finding Information Takes Too Long</h3><p>Need to know whether a customer has paid? Searching through several Excel files, WhatsApp messages, or printed receipts shouldn't be part of the process.</p><p>A modern business system lets you search for a customer, invoice, payment, or order in seconds, giving your team faster access to accurate information.</p><h3>3. Your Team Is Using Different Versions</h3><p>One employee updates the sales report. Another edits a second version. Someone else sends a third, final version.</p><p>When multiple versions of the same spreadsheet exist, nobody knows which one is correct.</p><p>Business software keeps everyone working from a single, live source of truth.</p><h3>4. Reports Take Hours to Prepare</h3><p>Many businesses spend days at the end of every month preparing reports. Data has to be collected, cleaned, checked, and combined before managers can make decisions.</p><p>With the right software, reports are generated automatically using live business data, allowing managers to focus on decisions instead of calculations.</p><h3>5. Growth Is Becoming Difficult</h3><p>What works for one employee may not work for ten. What works for fifty customers may not work for five thousand.</p><p>As your business grows, manual processes become slower, more expensive, and harder to manage. Business software is designed to scale, allowing your operations to grow without adding unnecessary administrative work.</p><h3>The Real Cost of Staying with Spreadsheets</h3><p>Many businesses delay investing in software because they see it as an expense. But the real cost often comes from continuing with manual processes:</p><ul><li>Lost productivity.</li><li>Human errors.</li><li>Duplicate work.</li><li>Slow customer service.</li><li>Delayed reporting.</li><li>Poor visibility into business performance.</li></ul><p>Over time, these hidden costs can exceed the price of implementing a proper system.</p><h3>Making the Case Internally</h3><p>If you're proposing new software within your organization, don't focus only on technology. Focus on business outcomes. Ask questions like:</p><ul><li>How many hours are spent on manual work each week?</li><li>How often do errors require correction?</li><li>How quickly can managers access reliable reports?</li><li>What happens if a key employee is unavailable?</li><li>Can the current process support future growth?</li></ul><p>When these questions are answered honestly, the value of automation becomes much clearer.</p><h3>Final Thoughts</h3><p>Spreadsheets are an excellent starting point, but they shouldn't become a permanent operating system for a growing business.</p><p>The right software reduces manual work, improves accuracy, provides real-time insights, and allows teams to spend more time serving customers instead of managing files. Upgrading isn't just about replacing spreadsheets - it's about building a business that is efficient, scalable, and ready for long-term growth.</p>"
    },
    'multi-page-launch': {
      title: "Adalyn Technologies Is Now a Multi-Page Platform",
      meta: "July 2026 &middot; 2 min read",
      body: "<p>We're excited to announce the launch of the new Adalyn Technologies website.</p><p>What started as a simple landing page has evolved into a fully featured, multi-page company website designed to better showcase who we are, what we build, and how we help businesses grow through technology.</p><h3>Why We Made the Change</h3><p>As our portfolio expanded, we realized a single page could no longer tell our story effectively.</p><p>Clients wanted to explore our services, view completed projects, read technical insights, and understand our development process before getting in touch.</p><p>A multi-page website gives every service and solution the space it deserves.</p><h3>What's New?</h3><p>The new platform introduces dedicated pages for:</p><ul><li>Our software development services.</li><li>Industry solutions.</li><li>Product portfolio.</li><li>Client success stories.</li><li>Technical blog and insights.</li><li>Company information.</li><li>Contact and consultation requests.</li></ul><p>This structure makes it easier to navigate the site and quickly find the information you need.</p><h3>A Better Experience for Clients</h3><p>Our goal has always been to build software that solves real business problems. The new website reflects that same philosophy.</p><p>Whether you're looking for a custom business system, a school management platform, M-Pesa integration, or a complete digital transformation partner, you can now explore our capabilities in greater detail before starting a conversation with us.</p><h3>Looking Ahead</h3><p>This launch is just the beginning. We'll continue publishing practical articles, sharing product updates, showcasing client projects, and introducing new solutions designed to help organizations operate more efficiently.</p><p>Thank you to everyone who has supported Adalyn Technologies on this journey. We're excited for what's next, and we look forward to building innovative software that powers businesses across Kenya and beyond.</p>"
    },
    'student-deployment': {
      title: "A Final Year Student's Guide to Deploying Your Project",
      meta: "July 2026 &middot; 5 min read",
      body: "<p>Completing your final year project is a huge achievement, but one mistake many students make is stopping after the application works on their laptop.</p><p>During project presentations, examiners don't just evaluate what you built - they also look at how practical and complete your solution is. A project that anyone can access through a live link often creates a stronger impression than one that only runs on your computer.</p><h3>Why Deployment Matters</h3><p>Imagine telling your examiner that it works, but only on your laptop. Now compare that with being able to say they can test it right now using a live link.</p><p>The second project immediately feels more professional. It demonstrates confidence, preparation, and an understanding of how real software is delivered.</p><h3>What Examiners Want to See</h3><p>Most examiners are looking for more than just working code. They want evidence that you understand the complete software development process. A strong project should include:</p><ul><li>A working application.</li><li>A responsive user interface.</li><li>A secure database.</li><li>Proper authentication.</li><li>Clear documentation.</li><li>A live deployment that can be demonstrated without setup.</li></ul><p>These are the qualities that make a student project feel like a real product.</p><h3>Choosing the Right Hosting Platform</h3><p>Today, deploying a web application is easier than ever. Cloud platforms allow students to publish their projects in just a few steps without buying expensive servers. A typical deployment includes:</p><ul><li>Your application hosted online.</li><li>A cloud database.</li><li>A custom or generated web address.</li><li>Automatic HTTPS security.</li><li>Continuous updates from GitHub.</li></ul><p>Once deployed, your examiner can access your project from any device with an internet connection.</p><h3>Prepare Before You Deploy</h3><p>Before publishing your project, make sure you have:</p><ul><li>Removed test data and unnecessary files.</li><li>Stored passwords and API keys securely using environment variables.</li><li>Fixed obvious bugs and broken links.</li><li>Tested the application on both desktop and mobile devices.</li><li>Verified that all core features work correctly.</li></ul><p>Deployment should be the final step - not the testing phase.</p><h3>Don't Forget Documentation</h3><p>Even the best application needs clear documentation. Include a README or user guide explaining:</p><ul><li>What the project does.</li><li>Technologies used.</li><li>Installation instructions.</li><li>Login credentials for demonstration.</li><li>Key features and screenshots.</li></ul><p>Good documentation makes your work easier to understand and demonstrates professionalism.</p><h3>Think Beyond Graduation</h3><p>Your final year project doesn't have to end after your presentation. A deployed project can become:</p><ul><li>Your portfolio piece.</li><li>A startup idea.</li><li>A freelance product.</li><li>A solution for real clients.</li><li>Proof of your technical skills during job interviews.</li></ul><p>Many successful software products started as university projects that continued to evolve.</p><h3>Final Thoughts</h3><p>Building the application is only part of the journey. Deploying it shows that you understand how software is delivered in the real world.</p><p>A live, accessible project demonstrates confidence, technical maturity, and attention to detail - qualities that stand out to examiners, employers, and future clients alike. Don't let your project live only on your laptop. Put it online, share it with confidence, and let your work speak for itself.</p>"
    }
  };

  function openArticle(key) {
    const article = articles[key];
    if (!article) return;
    document.getElementById('articleModalContent').innerHTML =
      '<div class="article-modal-meta">' + article.meta + '</div>' +
      '<h2>' + article.title + '</h2>' +
      article.body;
    document.getElementById('articleModalOverlay').classList.add('open');
    document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
  }

  function closeArticle() {
    document.getElementById('articleModalOverlay').classList.remove('open');
    document.body.style.overflow = '';
  }
</script>

  <script src="main.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
